codelists.name: Parameter Type
codelists.preferredTerm: Parameter Type: Indicates whether the parameter is derived as a function of one or more other parameters.

terms.preferredTerm: Derived: Indicates that a parameter is derived as a function of one or more other parameters.

codelists.name: Date Imputation Flag
codelists.preferredTerm: Date Imputation Flag: Indicates the level of imputation reflected in a date value.

terms.preferredTerm: Year Imputed: Entire date (year, month and day) is imputed.
Month Imputed: Month and day are imputed.
Day Imputed: Day is imputed.

codelists.name: Time Imputation Flag
codelists.preferredTerm: Time Imputation Flag: Indicates the level of imputation reflected in a time value.

terms.preferredTerm: Minutes Imputed: Minutes and seconds are imputed.
Seconds Imputed: Seconds are imputed.
Hours Imputed: Entire time (hours, minutes and seconds) is imputed.

codelists.name: Derivation Type
codelists.preferredTerm: Derivation Type: Analysis value derivation method.

terms.preferredTerm: Maximum Likelihood: A data imputation technique which populates missing values with estimates that maximize the probability of observing what has in fact been observed.
Last Observation Carried Forward: A data imputation technique which populates missing values with the subject's previous nonmissing value.
Worst Observation Carried Forward: A data imputation technique which populates missing values with the subject's worst-case nonmissing value.
Screening Observation Carried Forward: A data imputation technique which populates missing values with the subject's nonmissing screening observation.
Baseline Observation Carried Forward: A data imputation technique which populates missing values with the subject's nonmissing baseline observation.
Worst Case: A data imputation technique which populates missing values with the worst possible outcome.
Mean of Other Group: A data imputation technique which populates missing values with the mean value from a comparator or reference group.
Penultimate Observation Carried Forward: A data imputation technique which populates missing values with the subject's next-to-last nonmissing value.
Worst Observed Value in a Group: A data imputation technique which populates missing values with the worst value observed in a group of subjects.
Mean Observed Value in a Group: A data imputation technique which populates missing values with the mean value observed in a group of subjects.
Interpolation: A method of imputation involving a missing value that is between known values and is estimated by a function of those known values.
Average: A data derivation technique which calculates a subject's average value over a defined set of records.
Endpoint: A data derivation technique which calculates a subject's analysis end point value.
Minimum: A data derivation technique which calculates a subject's minimum value over a defined set of records.
Maximum: A data derivation technique which calculates a subject's maximum value over a defined set of records.
Best Case: A data imputation technique which populates missing values with the best possible outcome.
Best Observation Carried Forward: A data imputation technique which populates missing values with the subject's best-case nonmissing value.
